20.html">希捷卡</a>。但是，现在，您有一个更实惠的选择。 Western Digital <a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Western Digital;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=92bbc6e1-f32c-4060-9f86-b3358db79a39&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Western+Digital&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAbRKq2X1bkx7J_2DykUyE3S-XBvj7CrbZySbqu23DcUW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.westerndigital.com%2Fproducts%2Fexternal-drives%2Fwd-black-c50-expansion-card-for-xbox-ssd%23WDBMPH5120ANC-WCSN" class="rapid-with-clickid">发布了</a>WD Black C50 扩展卡系列，500GB 型号的起价为 80 美元。这比最近降价的 Seagate 同类产品低 10 美元，如果您只需要空间来玩一些额外的游戏，则更容易证明是合理的。一张 1TB 卡的售价与其同等大小的竞争对手相同，为 150 美元。</p><p> You&#39;ll need one of these proprietary add-ons if you want to add space for ready-to-play Xbox Series X/S games, which require solid-state drive cards that are as quick as the SSD built into the console. Conventional external USB drives can only be used to archive games or play Xbox One titles. That&#39;s fine if you only have a handful of active games at a time, but you&#39;ll want an Xbox-native card if you want access to many titles at short notice.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> These cards are still costlier than the NVMe SSDs you can <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-ps5-ssd-expansion-upgrade-150052315.html">buy for a PlayStation 5</a> . However, the price gap is now small enough that the storage format probably won&#39;t affect your choice of system. It&#39;s only an issue if you want 2TB of additional capacity. Western Digital doesn&#39;t offer a 2TB C50 card, and Seagate&#39;s $280 Xbox option is decidedly more expensive than PS5 options like Sabrent&#39;s $160 NVMe drive. </p><p><core-commerce id="53e93c1d77994cbdb76f46370a2eec68" data-type="product-list"></core-commerce></p><p></p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/western-digitals-first-xbox-series-xs-storage-cards-start-at-80-171723507.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/western-digitals-first-xbox-series-xs-storage-cards-start-at-80-171723507.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 27faddb5-4623-429c-91fd-903f4932847e</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 06 Jun 2023 17:17:23 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686071844</ingested><modified> 2023-06-06T17:17:27+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Jon Fingas]]></category><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/f5913600-0485-11ee-996f-d526ddc9193c" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1280" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/f5913600-0485-11ee-996f-d526ddc9193c" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Western Digital]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[WD Black C50 Xbox Series X/S storage card]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[WD Black C50 Xbox Series X/S storage card]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Chinese startup says its new EV battery doesn’t lose range in the cold]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> The Chinese startup Greater Bay Technology claims its latest EV battery can charge at normal speeds even in cold temperatures. Huang Xiangdong, co-founder and chairman, says the company&#39;s new Phoenix cell uses superconducting materials and thermal management to heat from -4F to 77F in only five minutes, allowing the battery to charge “within six minutes in all weather conditions,” <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-06-06/chinese-unicorn-claims-breakthrough-with-all-weather-ev-battery">according to</a> <em>Bloomberg</em> . “The Phoenix battery not only addresses the long charging time for EVs, but other pain points,” Huang said. “It doesn&#39;t matter if it&#39;s a hot day or a cold day, the Phoenix battery&#39;s range won&#39;t be affected.”</p><p> A loss of charging efficiency in cold weather has been a persistent obstacle in the EV battery space. Other automakers, including <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/polestar-2-single-motor-variant-cheaper-161752298.html">Polestar</a> and <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/g-ms-ev-heat-pump-can-extend-range-up-to-10-percent-130024466.html">GM</a> , have tackled the problem by adding heat pumps — and German company ZF even prototyped a <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/z-fs-exothermic-seat-belts-could-help-e-vs-go-15-percent-further-004553001.html">heated seat belt</a> (or “heat belt”) to reduce the energy used for cabin heating.</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> The new Phoenix cell allegedly has a range of 1,000 km (621 miles). The company expects to launch the battery to the public next year in electric vehicles from Aion, China&#39;s third most popular EV brand. (Aion falls under the umbrella of the state-owned Guangzhou Automobile Corporation, which Greater Bay Technology is incubated within.) In addition, Greater Bay Technology is reportedly “in talks with other carmakers to use the cell.” Summarizing Huang&#39;s long-term vision, he said, “Once EVs can be driven and maintained like gasoline cars, then there&#39;s a greater chance for mass adoption.”</p><p> Greater Bay Technology is a two-year-old startup valued at over $1 billion. Its first-generation battery is an extreme fast-charging cell currently equipped in Aion&#39;s V Plus electric SUV.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/chinese-startup-says-its-new-ev-battery-doesnt-lose-range-in-the-cold-164149959.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/chinese-startup-says-its-new-ev-battery-doesnt-lose-range-in-the-cold-164149959.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e6200429-e9b0-409b-b918-265b62e20303</guid><dc:creator> Will Shanklin</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 06 Jun 2023 16:41:49 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1686075402</ingested><modified> 2023-06-06T18:16:47+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="1702" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e9043580-0486-11ee-b43f-b7ee5325bc7f" width="2838"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1702" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e9043580-0486-11ee-b43f-b7ee5325bc7f" width="2838"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Greater Bay Technology]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Re